denvy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/img-logo.png\" style=\"height: auto; padding: 0; width: 180px\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr ><td class=\"one-column\" style=\"padding:0; \" ><table bgcolor=\"#292E4B\" class=\"bg-dpurple mktEditable\" id=\"headerText\" style=\"-moz-osx-font-smoothing:grayscale; -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased; background:#292E4B; border-spacing:0; color:#6D6E71; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; \" width=\"100%\" ><tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" class=\"inner contents\" style=\"padding: 0px 30px 30px; text-align: left; width: 100%\">\r\n<h1 style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 42px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px;\">What\'s New with Che</h1>\r\n<p style=\"color: #ababc1; font-size: 20px; line-height: 22px; Margin-top: 10px;\">Technical blogs, release notes, community and more.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr ><td class=\"one-column\" style=\"padding:0; \" ><table class=\"mktEditable\" id=\"textArea1\" style=\"-moz-osx-font-smoothing:grayscale; -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased; border-spacing:0; color:#6D6E71; font-family:Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; \" width=\"100%\" ><tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" class=\"inner contents\" style=\"padding: 10px 30px; text-align: left; width: 100%\">\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\"color: #525C86; font-size: 32px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px\">Insight: The State of Eclipse Che</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; Margin: 0 0 30px\">Six months after beta launch, Che has built a thriving ecosystem of contributors and partners, with tens of thousands of downloads each week. We’re at an inflection point as development is poised to be the next great migration to the cloud.</p>\r\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\r\n\"http://mkto-ab050050.com/f00Cb0P0Ai001Y2iA9Ybr0g\" style=\"Margin-bottom: 15px; background: #FDB940; border-radius: 4px; color: #fff; font-size: 20px; display: inline-block; line-height: 45px; max-width: 300px; padding-left: 10%; padding-right: 10%; text-decoration: none\"\r\n>Read the Blog</a>\r\n<hr style=\"border-color: #eeeeee; border-style: solid; border-width: 10px 0 0\">\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\"color: #525C86; font-size: 32px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px\">Step-by-Step: Guide to How Workspace Servers Work</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; Margin: 0 0 30px\">Eclipse Che defines the workspace to be the project code files and all of their dependencies necessary to edit, build, run, and debug them.</p>\r\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\r\n\"http://mkto-ab050050.com/G1Y0YC20AcgjA0bP0000r9i\" style=\"Margin-bottom: 15px; background: #FDB940; border-radius: 4px; color: #fff; font-size: 20px; display: inline-block; line-height: 45px; max-width: 300px; padding-left: 10%; padding-right: 10%; text-decoration: none\"\r\n>Read the Doc</a>\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\"color: #525C86; font-size: 32px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px\">Hands-On: Configure and Run Plain Java Apps in Che</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; Margin: 0 0 30px\">Develop and run standard Java applications by creating and running a simple “Hello World” example using one of the Che template apps. Then clone a plain Java project from git, configure the classpath, add a library to classpath and run the application.</p>\r\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\r\n\"http://mkto-ab050050.com/kA0dP0900Cr02YbiA10kg0Y\" style=\"Margin-bottom: 15px; background: #FDB940; border-radius: 4px; color: #fff; font-size: 20px; display: inline-block; line-height: 45px; max-width: 300px; padding-left: 10%; padding-right: 10%; text-decoration: none\"\r\n>Read the Blog</a>\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\"color: #525C86; font-size: 32px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px\">Hands-On: Develop, Run and Debug Android Apps Natively</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; Margin: 0 0 30px\">Learn how to prepare your Android device for USB and wireless debugging in Eclipse Che.</p>\r\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\r\n\"http://mkto-ab050050.com/v0gA09Cl0bPYAre1Y02i000\" style=\"Margin-bottom: 15px; background: #FDB940; border-radius: 4px; color: #fff; font-size: 20px; display: inline-block; line-height: 45px; max-width: 300px; padding-left: 10%; padding-right: 10%; text-decoration: none\"\r\n>Read the Blog</a>\r\n<hr style=\"border-color: #eeeeee; border-style: solid; border-width: 10px 0 0\">\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\"color: #525C86; font-size: 32px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px\">Release Notes: Eclipse Che 4.5</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; Margin: 0 0 30px\">Eclipse Che 4.5 has been released with 84 issues resolved and updates including new workspace URL schema, configurable Docker API version and JGit implementation.</p>\r\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\r\n\"http://mkto-ab050050.com/v0gA09Cm0bPYArf1Y02i000\" style=\"Margin-bottom: 15px; background: #FDB940; border-radius: 4px; color: #fff; font-size: 20px; display: inline-block; line-height: 45px; max-width: 300px; padding-left: 10%; padding-right: 10%; text-decoration: none\"\r\n>Release Notes</a>\r\n<hr style=\"border-color: #eeeeee; border-style: solid; border-width: 10px 0 0\">\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\"color: #525C86; font-size: 32px; font-weight: normal; Margin-bottom: 10px\">Are you developing a project with Eclipse Che?</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; Margin: 0 0 30px\">Tell us about your development project and Che experience, and we\'ll feature it on our blog and social channels.</p>\r\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\r\n\"http://mkto-ab050050.com/G1Y0YC20AggnA0bP0000r9i\" style=\"Margin-bottom: 15px; background: #FDB940; border-radius: 4px; color: #fff; font-size: 20px; display: inline-block; line-height: 45px; max-width: 300px; padding-left: 10%; padding-right: 10%; text-decoration: none\"\r\n>Share Your Story</a>\r\n<h1 class=\"text-purple\" style=\