ost. File-Context Git Actions: File context menu for common git actions. PHP Composer: Support for the popular PHP scaffolding utility. Updated PHP Tutorial: Try all the new PHP intellisense and debugging. Memory &amp; Disk Checks on Startup: Resource checks when starting Che. Networking Checks on Startup: Checks browser to workspace and server to workspace connectivity to avoid common network issues. Improved CLI Output: More detail has been added to the info command plus you can generate a diagnostic snapshot for problems.  CPU Limiting for Docker Builds: Docker builds can be CPU intensive so they now carry CPU limits to prevent starving other workspaces. Restart a Failed Workspace: You can now easily restart workspaces that didn’t start correctly the first time. Python Intellisense: Syntax highlighting and hover-over help docs.  Other Great Features: You can read more about all the features of Eclipse Che 5.2 in the release note blog.  Automatic updates of workspace config Simplified Dashboard build Proper cache control header for resources Added Vert.x stack Improved find and navigate to file capabilities in IDE Allowed to get verbose mode on unison utility when using CLI sync command Add possibility to catch websocket url error Updated the styles for popups Add support of docker compose file in Chefile Input-boxes with ‘required’ attribute are marked with asterisk Add pretty formatting in bats tests CLI image and add bats-assert helper functions Added documentation  Read the Release Notes                 Eclipse Che Release Notes Changelog Get Eclipse Che Docs Source Code Eclipse Che is licensed under EPL 1.0.       &nbsp;    Eclipse Che - Codenvy 33 New Montgomery Suite 1500, San Francisco, CA 94105            This email was sent to lawren653815@gmail.com. If you no longer wish to receive these emails you may unsubscribe at any time.',1),
